Overview.Summary: The 2016 Kosovan presidential election (9, 11) resulted in Hashim Thaci being elected as the new President of Kosovo (1, 3, 9, 11, 17, 18). The election was contested by the opposition (2, 4, 8, 13, 19) and sparked violent protests (4, 5, 19). Thaci's victory was met with celebrations by his supporters (9). The election was part of a larger trend in presidential elections in 2016, including those in Uganda (10, 16), the United States (7), Zambia (6), and Taiwan (20). The new President's past involvement with organized crime was also brought to light (12). The election was seen as a test for national unity in the young country (11).
